{"title":"Canyon Lux Trail ‘downcountry’ bike gets new front triangle, slacker geo & more travel","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/19/canyon-lux-trail-downcountry-bike-gets-new-front-triangle-slacker-geo-more-travel/","date":1629363610000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Light, fast,&nbsp;<em>and</em> capable. That’s the Canyon Lux Trail in a nutshell, at least according to Canyon themselves. Modern XC mountain bikes are certainly capable, especially when compared to older machines, but&nbsp;<em>downcountry</em> bikes? Those are in another league when it comes to capability. One that Canyon is joining with their new Lux Trail.</p><p>It would have been easy for Canyon to simply slap a longer fork and some different components on the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/27/2021-canyon-lux-builds-up-full-suspension-29er-xc-bike-with-latest-race-ready-tech/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">existing Lux XC bike</a> and call it a day. Instead, Canyon went back to the drawing board and came up with an all-new front triangle. Mostly, this was done to enable a longer reach across frame sizes, but it also allowed them to dial in the geometry to adapt to the longer suspension travel.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022.jpg\" alt=\"Canyon Lux Trail geometry 2022\" width=\"762\" height=\"583\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022.jpg 762w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-297x227.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-120x92.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-696x533.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-549x420.jpg 549w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-80x60.jpg 80w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 762px) 100vw, 762px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022.jpg 762w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-297x227.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-120x92.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-696x533.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-549x420.jpg 549w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210533/Canyon-Lux-Trail-geometry-2022-80x60.jpg 80w\"></a></p><p>The result is a bike that is longer and slacker than the original, with reach numbers increased by about 20mm per size, and now runs a 67.5° head tube angle with a 74.5° seat tube angle. That geometry is paired with a shorter 60mm stem and 760mm wide bars for a fit that is more aggressive, but still XC-able.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7.jpg\" alt=\"rockshox rear suspension\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210612/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-7-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Suspension travel has been increased front and rear, with a 120mm travel suspension fork and 110mm of travel out back. The Lux Trail also gets burlier suspension forks, though still of the light weight variety with either RockShox SID 35mm or Fox StepCast 34mm platforms. Rear suspension duties are handled by either the RockShox Deluxe Ultimate RMT, or Fox Float DPS Factory RMT, both with dual remote lockouts that stiffen the suspension with one click or twist.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6.jpg\" alt=\"SRAM AXS drivetrain\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210606/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-6-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>At the back of the bike, the Lux Trail uses the same rear triangle as the current Lux. That means a pivot-less flex stay at the chainstay/seat tube junction keeps things light. The bikes still use Canyon’s Triple Phase suspension concept which is named for its three areas of focus – small bump compliance, a stable mid-stroke, and a ramp up at the end of the stroke to help control big hits. How big? The Lux Trail is rated to the same Category 3 standard as their longer travel trail bikes.</p><h2>IPU Steering</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10.jpg\" alt=\"Canyon Lux Trail IPU system\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210627/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-10-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>No one likes a broken top tube after a crash causes your shifter or brake levers to spin back and impact the frame. So the Canyon IPU (Impact Protection Unit) prevents that from happening. The steering stop is clamped to the steerer and prevents over rotation of the bars from damaging the frame — just remember that you have to loosen the IPU in order to tighten the headset.</p><h2>World’s Lightest Chainguide?</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11.jpg\" alt=\"Canyon Lux Trail chain guide\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210633/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-11-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>At just 3.7g, does the Lux Trail include the world’s lightest chainguide? We’re not sure, but it’s certainly not much additional weight for some added assurance that the chain will stay on the ring. Technically, it’s 8.7g if you include the 5g screw…</p><h2>Real Room for Bottles!</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1.jpg\" alt=\"room for two water bottles in the Canyon Lux Trail \" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210538/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-1-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>While we’re on the topic of excellent features, let’s give Canyon credit for their excellent water bottle configuration. Apparently all sizes have room for two bottles inside the front triangle, with room for fairly large bottles. And even with two bottles in the frame, there’s still room up front to strap a tube, jacket, or flat pack.</p><h2>What’s it weigh?</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022.jpg\" alt=\"Canyon Lux Trail weight chart\" width=\"430\" height=\"445\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022.jpg 430w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022-290x300.jpg 290w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022-116x120.jpg 116w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022-406x420.jpg 406w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 430px) 100vw, 430px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022.jpg 430w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022-290x300.jpg 290w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022-116x120.jpg 116w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210649/Canyon-Lux-Trail-weight-chart-2022-406x420.jpg 406w\"></a></p><p>One of the ways ‘downcountry’ bikes differ from trail bikes is that there is still a big emphasis on it being extremely light. Compared to the Lux, the Lux Trail has about a 30g weight penalty on the frame due to the longer front end, at a claimed 1,905g for a medium frame. Canyon even goes to lengths to break that down to the gram for all the various parts that make up the frame.</p><p>As for the actual complete weight, Cory’s Lux Trail 7 test bike in a size large came in at 12.43kg/27.40lb including a pair of 340g Crankbrothers Candy 3 pedals, 100g of Canyon Sideloader bottle cages, and tire sealant. Canyon’s claimed weight on this build is listed as 11.7kg. The lightest build is the Lux Trail CF 9 Emily Batty Edition which is claimed as 10.9kg.</p><h2>Frame Details</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13.jpg\" alt=\"Canyon Lux Trail frame\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210644/Canyon-Lux-Trail-mountain-bike-XC-2022-13-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>To keep the internal cable routing simple, you’ll find internal tubes the length of the frame allowing cables and hoses to pop out the other side. You’ll still find a Quixle, quick release thru axle out back, and Boost spacing front and rear. Tire clearance is recommended as 2.4″ up front and 2.35″ out back on a 30mm rim. Additional details include a ZS44/IS52 headset and a pressfit bottom bracket.</p><h2>Models, Pricing, and Availability</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022.jpg\" alt=\"Canyon Lux Trail build specifications\" width=\"1385\" height=\"438\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022.jpg 1385w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-297x94.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-800x253.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-120x38.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-768x243.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-696x220.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-1068x338.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-1328x420.jpg 1328w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1385px) 100vw, 1385px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022.jpg 1385w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-297x94.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-800x253.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-120x38.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-768x243.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-696x220.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-1068x338.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/18210529/Canyon-Lux-Trail-build-kits-2022-1328x420.jpg 1328w\"></a></p><p>The Lux Trail will be offered in four different builds, and all of them will be available in all markets. Pricing starts at $3,999 for the Shimano SLX and Fox Equipped Lux Trail CF 6, and tops out at $6,999 for the Shimano XTR equipped Emily Batty Edition. One of the only changes for the U.S. market will be longer dropper posts with 150mm travel droppers on everything but the CF 8 which will feature a 125mm Reverb AXS post. U.S. bikes also get RaceFace cockpits.</p><ul><li>Lux Trail CF 6 $3,999<u></u><u></u></li><li>Lux Trail CF 7 $5,299<u></u><u></u></li><li>Lux Trail CF 8 $6,299<u></u><u></u></li><li>Lux Trail CF 9 EB Edition $6,999</li></ul><p>In Europe, bikes will be available for purchase this week. For us in America, we’ll have to wait a bit longer with no date specified other than they&nbsp;<em>are</em> coming.</p><p>How does the Canyon Lux Trail perform on the… trail? <a href=\"https://wp.me/pcUhB6-17S9\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hit up Cory’s review here to find out.&nbsp;</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.canyon.com/en-us/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>canyon.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"978fed5683dccf36ef405e9278bf6b548f25390febdb505d2ff78aab0e59dfb6","category":"Cycling"}